      "id": 1,
      "text": "Williamsburg began as part of Bushwick, was annexed by Brooklyn in 1855, then grew into its own city before merging back.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        21
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://nyc.eu/boroughs-of-new-york-city/brooklyn/williamsburg/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The neighborhood was named Williamsburgh—later shortened to Williamsburg—after military engineer Jonathan Williams who mapped the area in the early 1800s.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Williamsburg%2C_Brooklyn"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Chemist Charles Pfizer founded Pfizer Pharmaceutical in Williamsburg, keeping an industrial plant there until 2007 before moving headquarters to Manhattan.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Williamsburg%2C_Brooklyn"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Charles Pratt’s family established Pratt Institute, a renowned art and architecture school, and the nearby Astral Oil Works that later joined Standard Oil.",
